Fast pizza. Tasty pizza. All with a smile.  Fast: Once you walk in, you are asked for your name and the type of pizza you'd like - BYO or one of their specials. At the end of the line, pizza goes in the hot hot oven and two minutes later, it's done.  Tasty: So many varieties. For the sauce (red, spicy red, white, pesto), for cheese (parmesan, mozzarella, ovalini mozzarella, gorgonzola, etc.), for meat (meatballs, chicken, pepperoni, etc.), for veggies (peppers, onion, pineapple, spinach, basil, etc.) and finally the drizzle (ranch, pesto, balsamic vinegar, etc.). The drizzle is my favorite topped with some arugula. Yum.  All with a smile: Everytime I've come here, whether they're busy or not, I've always had patient and kind customer service. And that's commendable especially at a place with unlimited toppings!  Tip: Eat your pizza in store, the crust/base is super crunchy right out of the oven!

I am a big fan of the Blaze franchise, but a disappointing visit to this location spoiled what would have been an otherwise delicious meal. The staff preparing the food was excellent and moved me swiftly through the line, but once it came out of the oven I had to wait for 15 minutes before being taken care of. The employee who put the finishing touches on my pizza was inconsiderate and due to his slow pace, my food was cold by the time it was in my hands. I will continue to eat at these restaurants, but not at this establishment.

Ordered a to-go order via the one, which is a 3rd part service. They got my order, we showed up to pick up the meal, everything is solid.  Expect it’s not. They missed an putting an entire pizza into one of our pizza boxes. Like, we order 6 pizzas, got 6 pizza boxes, and only got 5 pizzas.  In most circumstances this is fine. I called the place up, they apologized, and said they’d refund just that pizza since it was pouring rain out and I wasn’t about to make another 45 minutes run out to just get one pizza.  However, over a week later, and still no refund. No call from the store, no explanation. I was promised a call from a manager and a refund within a day or so and I didn’t. Now I’m not one to scream and yell and “ask for the manager”, but I also have to recognize that not every Blaze is awesome (though this is a first for me), and when I’m promised a refund for a big inconvenience like being the only one at our party without a dinner to eat, that I’d enjoy having some explanation about what happened.  Moving forward, I’ll go out of my way to visit other Blaze pizzas around Boston.
